  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published by Leuven University Press in 2022, \"Stilte in de klas\" provides a detailed exploration of silence in the classroom environment, highlighting pedagogical implications. Despite not currently showing citations or public discourse on social media platforms, the work suggests a significant emphasis on commercial linkage through its presence on Amazon and Goodreads.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Stilte in de klas,\" released by Leuven University Press in 2022, presents a nuanced examination of silence as a crucial factor in educational settings. While quantitative impact metrics such as citations and mentions across various platforms indicate limited academic and societal discourse so far, the work is strategically positioned in commercial spaces like Amazon and Goodreads. This suggests a potential for grassroots engagement and wider readership among individuals interested in pedagogical practices.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">The absence of OpenAlex citations or community discussions highlights an opportunity for future engagement. The lack of mentions on platforms like Wikipedia, Reddit, and Bluesky indicates that while the work is foundational, it has not yet penetrated broader public or academic conversations. This gap may serve as a call to action for educators and researchers to consider the thematic significance of silence in classrooms and how it can inform teaching strategies.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Moreover, the text's implications extend to policy discussions, with evidence of sustainability and relevance to global educational goals, reflected in its association with one Sustainable Development Goal (SDG). This connection underscores the potential for \"Stilte in de klas\" to influence not only teaching practices but also educational policy more broadly.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">As it stands, the work illustrates essential themes in education that merit further exploration and discussion, serving as a springboard for potential initiatives aimed at enhancing classroom dynamics. Moving forward, the academic community might benefit from fostering discussions and collaborations around the concepts introduced in this volume to fully unlock its potential impact.</p>",
